2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The proposed hybrid model combines a physics engine with an object-based neural network, which falls under the domain of machine learning.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The use of neural networks for dynamics modeling and control is a common application of AI in robotics.
4. cs.CV (Computer Vision): Although not the main focus of the paper, computer vision techniques may be used in conjunction with the proposed model for object recognition and tracking.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with control problems involving complex contact dynamics, which is a topic within systems and control.
